<header>
  <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
    <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">ColorSpace</a>
    <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbarNavAltMarkup" aria-controls="navbarNavAltMarkup" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
      <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
    </button>
    <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNavAltMarkup">
      <div class="navbar-nav">
        <a class="nav-item nav-link" href="/spaces">Back to Profile</a>
        <a class="nav-item nav-link" href="/auth/logout">Logout</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>
</header>

<h2><%= space.name %></h2>

<hr />

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-6 col-xs-6">
      <img src="<%= space.url %>" class="show-image">
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-6 col-xs-6">
      <h4>Notes:</h4>
      <p class="space-notes"><%= space.note %></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr />

<div class="all-swatches col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
    <% space.colors.forEach(function(color) { %>
      <div class="swatches">
        <div class="front" style="background:<%= color.hex %>;">
          <footer class="color-details">
            <h6>COLOR</h6>
            <span><%= color.hex %></span>
          </footer>
        </div>
        <div class="back">
          <p>RGB <span><%= color.r %>,<%= color.g %>,<%= color.b %></span></p>
          <p>CMYK <span><%= color.c %>,<%= color.m %>,<%= color.y %>,<%= color.k %></span></p>
          <p>HEX <span><%= color.hex %></span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% }); %>
</div>

<hr />

<div class="container">
  <div class="card border-dark mb-3 show-cards" style="max-width: 20rem;">
    <div class="card-header">Bold Colors</div>
    <div class="card-body text-dark">
      <h4 class="card-title">Add richness to your space</h4>
      <p class="card-text">Bright or bold colors are often used as accent colors.
        These colors should be used sparingly to add a pop of color in a space.
        They are often not recomended for large painted areas, but are perfect
        for small accent pieces such as decorative vases or throw pillows.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card border-dark mb-3 show-cards" style="max-width: 20rem;">
    <div class="card-header">Neutral Colors</div>
    <div class="card-body text-dark">
      <h4 class="card-title">Scale well for larger application</h4>
      <p class="card-text"> Neutral colors can be applied to many areas as
        they are gentle on the eyes and pair easily with brighter colors.
        Most are various tones of white, off-white or light gray.
        These colors are often recomended for large painted areas, outdoor spaces,
        window treatments, and trim.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card border-dark mb-3 show-cards" style="max-width: 20rem;">
    <div class="card-header">Everything Else</div>
    <div class="card-body text-dark">
      <h4 class="card-title">With medium depth comes versitility</h4>
      <p class="card-text">These colors are neither bold nor neutral, but fall somewhere
        in between. They can be vibrant or subdued tones and will make up the bulk of your color palate.
        these colors are often recomended for painted accent walls, furniture, area rugs, throw pillows, or bedding.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
